Poland Supports U.N. Chief 's Mission in Iraq
WARSAW , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Poland supports United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan 's efforts to solve the weapons inspection crisis in Iraq , and hopes there will be a satisfactory outcome to the situation in the Gulf region , a Foreign Ministry spokesman said Thursday .
The spokesman , Pawel Dobrowolski , said the Polish government believed that only by fully implementing the agreement reached between Kofi Annan and Iraq can the economic sanctions imposed on Baghdad be lifted .
On February 23 , Dobrowolski said Poland welcomed the U.N . - Iraq agreement .
Earlier , Poland had backed the United States using military force against Iraq .
